node.text:
It’s been one year since we all lost Hawaii’s first World Champ, Derek Ho. His legacy will live on forever as The King of Pipeline! On Friday, July 23rd (9am) we will pay respect and celebrate his life out at Pipe. Sending prayers and positive light to the Ho ohana. We love and miss you Uncle D 🙏🏽❤️🌟#TrueToThis
🎸:@gavinbeschen808

node.text: @shunmurakami_mobb currently sitting in 4th place on the World Qualifying Tour, with surfing like this it’s easy to see why! 🎥 @hajime0326

Over a year and a half in the making and featuring a cast of surfing’s most capable and compelling characters, anticipation is peaking for the release of Volcom Stone’s latest feature surf film, Psychic Migrations. Following 2014’s True To This, a surf-skate-snow epic, the forthcoming Psychic Migrations is yet another inspired Veeco Production that builds on more than 20 years and 30 influential films from the world of Volcom. Directed by veteran surf filmmaker Ryan Thomas and shot on location in the West Indies, East Indies, Australia, Polynesia, and the Americas, the film weaves the physical expression of riding a rousing score of waves with a cerebral odyssey through the scapes and textures travelled to find them.

Starring: Dusty Payne, Mitch Coleborn, Yago Dora, Nate Tyler, Carlos Muñoz, Ryan Burch, Andrew Doheny, Parker Coffin, Alex Gray, Balaram Stack, Mike Gleason, Miguel Tudela, Joan Duru, Imai Devault, Tom Dosland, Gavin Beschen, Ozzie Wright and Kelly Slater.  #TrueToThis

node.text:
The anthem of a generation that even today, still rings True To This.  The first of its kind, this film galvanized Volcom as Americas First Boarding Company.  There is just one problem, in 1993 licensing music for a VHS release was a lot different than the digital abyss of now.

But we have you covered with a Spotify playlist of the original soundtrack -> vol.cm/awrplaylist

Just like driving a stick shift, grab your boombox and watch this in manual!  Or pop on your favorite playlist… Or create a new one all together and put your personal stamp on it!  #TrueToThis #AliveWeRide
